Forum Post: 
Post title: upload materials from command line
Post description: Hi all. I have to upload a file to roughly 200 courses and I'm looking for a way to avoid doing it course by course. Is there a plugin to help me do it, something like an upload from command line? I searched for hints but I wasn't able to find any information. Grazie Luca
Comments associated with the post: 
Comment 1: Hi Luca, How about checking out the command line tool Moosh . It includes a command to restore a backup into an existing course.
Comment 2: Hi Luca There is also a utility included with the Moodle installation at admin/cli/restore_backup.php. You just create a resource back it up, upload backup file to server account, and then run that with the file and course id specified by command line options.
Comment 3: Thanks Daniel, an utility included in Moodle sounds even better than Moosh! Does it allow you to restore a backup into a course (to create a file resource in the course) as well as into a category (to create a new course)?
Comment 4: Hi Helen, The restore_backup.php script was added in Moodle 3.11. Moosh is much older, but has a lot of other functions. You need to create the resource normally. You can manually create an activity backup, download it from Moodle and upload to the server, or you can use the backup.php(Moodle 2.7) script to create a backup on the command line. You need to supply backup.php with resource's module id and a filename. Then you supply filename and course id for the target course. Actually I just noticed there is also an import.php (Moodle 4.4) command that should copy the resource to a new course in one line, but I have not tried it. Several great scripts have been added gradually. Unfortunately if you were not aware of them, then they are not documented as they ought. There is very brief mention of backup/restore in Administration via command line . and import and other commands are missing. Daniel
Comment 5: You can supply a category Id to restore_backup.php. I think that will restore a course backup to a new course. You can delete a course with delete_course.php (Moodle 4.1).
Comment 6: Helen, I added documentation for import and delete script if you want to check that. I added information for import into Course copy page, but technically the script does not duplicate the course it only merges content into existing courses so that may need to be moved elsewhere.
