Comment 8: Hello Lucas, how are you? 😊 What an interesting challenge you've brought to the forum! I always enjoy solving these cases by using a PHP script that automates the process and creates activities in a customized way, as needed. And the best part: it gives me total control and efficiency! 🚀 Here’s an overview of how I usually handle this: I create `.php` files that perform the necessary actions. First, I call the native `create_course()` function to create the course and trigger the necessary events. 
```text
<?php

require_once("../config.php");
require_once("{$CFG->
dirroot
}/course/lib.php");
require_once("{$CFG->dirroot}/mod/resource/lib.php");
require_once(__DIR__ . "/lib.php");
require_once("{$CFG->dirroot}/course/modlib.php");

$file = "/path/to/your/file/my_file.pdf"; // Path to the file to be uploaded
$courses = [2, 3, 4]; // Course IDs

foreach ($courses as $courseid) {
    $
context
 = context_course::instance($courseid);
    $fs = get_file_storage();

    $fileinfo = [
        "contextid" => $context->id,
        "component" => "mod_resource",
        "filearea" => "content",
        "itemid" => 0,
        "filepath" => "/",
        "filename" => "my_file.pdf"
    ];

    $draftitemid = $fs->create_file_from_pathname($fileinfo, $file);

    $data = new stdClass();
    $data->course = $courseid;
    $data->name = "Resource Name";
    $data->intro = "";
    $data->introformat = FORMAT_HTML;
    $data->coursemodule = create_course_module($courseid, "resource", 1);
    $data->files = $draftitemid;

    // Set the display options to the site defaults.
    $config = get_config("resource");
    $data->display = $config->display;
    $data->popupheight = $config->popupheight;
    $data->popupwidth = $config->popupwidth;
    $data->printintro = $config->printintro;
    $data->showsize = (isset($config->showsize)) ? $config->showsize : 0;
    $data->showtype = (isset($config->showtype)) ? $config->showtype : 0;
    $data->showdate = (isset($config->showdate)) ? $config->showdate : 0;
    $data->filterfiles = $config->filterfiles;

    resource_add_instance($data, null);

    echo "File successfully uploaded to course ID {$courseid}! \n";
}

function create_course_module($course, $modulename, $sectionid) {
    list($module, $context, $cw, $cm, $data) = prepare_new_moduleinfo_data($course, $modulename, $sectionid);

    $coursemodule = $data->id = add_course_module($data);

    return $coursemodule;
}
```
 After running this script, the PDF file will be added to the three courses! You can further customize this by adding descriptions, setting permissions, and even notifying students. Eduardo Kraus Professor and Programmer
