Comment 12: Since moosh was mentioned ... moosh command: module-config Description: Copy a module from one course to another. Example 1: Copy module id 27 to course id 34. moosh module-copy 27 34 Example 2: Copy module id 27 to course id 34 and name the new module "Assignment 1". moosh module-copy --name "Assignment 1" 27 34 Example 3: Copy module id 27 to course id 34 and name the new module "Assignment 1", placing it in section 2. moosh -n module-copy --name "Assignment 1" --section 2 27 34 For multiples - 1 mod to multiple courses, one could create a courses ID list consisting of one line course ID numbers and then loop Example 1 above through the course ID's moosh -n module-copy 27 $cid getcids via db query mysql -u $mddbuser -p$mddbpass -e "use $mddbname;select id from mdl_course;" > cids.txt;cat cids.txt edit cids.txt file to remove the label at top and course ID 1 which is front page . Also remove any course id's where you do not want to import/reuse the mod. Create a non interactive looping shell script - you could change the moosh module-copy command to be executed ... below is an example: cd /path/to/your/code/admin/cli/; for i in `cat ./cids.txt` do echo "Course ID in que:" $i; moosh -n module-copy --name "Assignment 1" --section 2 27 $i done echo 'Done'; Again, change the moosh command above to one desired. Suggest you do just one to see how it works. Have used similar for restoring full courses to different categories with similar script. 'SoS', Ken
